'''Kniaginia''' is the feminine form of the [[Slavic]] word [[Kniaz']] \also spelt as ''kniaz'' or ''knyaz''\ , a royal title of the rulers of Slavic states and of the Slavic nobility of the royal blood, later in history used also as the honorary title bestoved by the [[Emperor]]s and the reigning [[Empress]]es of [[Russia]] on the persons of outstanding merit.